title: Lee Ganae Gimbap
description: Serves meat, veg options available. A family-owned restaurant in the basement of Hill Castle Plaza, 2 blocks from Incheon City Hall station. Seats 14. Specializes in gimbap and other bunshik fast Korean food. Vegan-optional dishes include: gimbap, jjeolmyeon (chewy spicy buckwheat noodles), and ddeokbokki (spicy rice cake stew).  Sun dubu (spicy tofu stew) and doen-jang jigae (fermented soybean paste stew) are available Monday, Tuesday, Thursday. Owner speaks English, Mandarin, Japanese.
